<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Stuffed Lamb with Spinach and Pine Nuts Recipe</title>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- The name of recipe by Gordon Ramsay -->>
    <h1>Stuffed Lamb with Spinach and Pine Nuts Recipe</h1>

    <!-- What's the recipe is -->
    <p>
        Stuffed lamb with spinach and pine nuts is a flavorful and elegant dish perfect for 
        family dinners or special occasions. Tender lamb is filled with a delicious mixture of 
        spinach, feta cheese, garlic, onion, and crunchy pine nuts, then roasted to perfection.
    </p>

    <!-- Subheading for ingredients -->
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>

    <!-- Unordered list for ingredients -->
    <ul>
        <li>1 small onion, peeled and chopped</li>
        <li>2 garlic cloves, peeled and sliced</li>
        <li>Olive oil, for frying</li>
        <li>3 tbsp pine nuts</li>
        <li>250g young spinach, washed</li>
        <li>150g feta cheese, crumbled</li>
        <li>1 boned saddle of lamb (1.75–2kg)</li>
        <li>1–2 tsp sumac</li>
        <li>Sea salt and freshly ground black pepper</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Subheading for dressing -->
    <h2>Dressing Ingredients</h2>

    <!-- Unordered list for dressing -->
    <ul>
        <li>½ large cucumber, peeled, deseeded, and sliced</li>
        <li>150ml natural yoghurt</li>
        <li>Small bunch of mint, shredded</li>
        <li>1 tbsp pomegranate molasses</li>
        <li>Zest of 1 lemon</li>
        <li>Squeeze of lime</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Subheading for method -->
    <h2>Method</h2>

    <!-- Ordered list instructions for the recipe -->
    <ol>
        <li>Sauté the onion and garlic in olive oil for 5 minutes until softened.</li>
        <li>Add pine nuts and fry for 1 minute until golden.</li>
        <li>Add spinach and cook until wilted, then remove from heat and mix in feta cheese.</li>
        <li>Lay the lamb open on a board and season with salt, pepper, and sumac.</li>
        <li>Spoon the spinach mixture into the middle of the lamb.</li>
        <li>Roll the meat around the filling and tie with string.</li>
        <li>Chill for at least 30 minutes or overnight.</li>
        <li>Preheat the oven to 190°C / Gas 5.</li>
        <li>Brown the lamb in hot oil for 10 minutes.</li>
        <li>Roast in the oven for 45–55 minutes.</li>
        <li>Allow the lamb to rest before slicing.</li>
        <li>Mix dressing ingredients together.</li>
        <li>Serve sliced lamb with dressing on the side.</li>
    </ol>

</body>
</html>
